latestIgtvVideos.title: Breathing Exercises And Asanas to build your immunity.
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
These are simple exercises I did during my days of COVID, this routine only takes 5mins of your time and you can do it comfortably on your bed as well.
Points to be noticed :-
1.Always remember when you breathe in your stomach comes outside and goes in when u exhale.
2.For your Anulom Vilom : 
You start with blocking right side of the nose using your thumb and then breathe in from the left and close the left nostril using your ring finger or middle finger and then exhale from the right.
One round is completed when your repeat the above on both sides.
3.For Pavanmukht asana  you can also bring your head close to your knees,(if comfortable else let the head stay down ) try touching your nose to the knees.
4.For all the exercises done in the video you do as much as your body can take, don’t exert yourself and feel tired.
5.These are exercises that helped me a lot and is only a suggestion to you all, do as per your convenience.
Thank you for your patience.
Just a gesture of sharing & helping you🙏🏻
.
.
.
